              <h3>We hire creative, motivated designers &amp; developers</h3>
              <h4>Come work with us at Lone Star</h4>
            </div>
            <div class='container'>
              <div class='job'>
                <h5>Ruby Developer</h5>
                <p>
                  We&rsquo;ve been in Austin for 18 years, building complex web software for a diverse variety of businesses. We&rsquo;re looking to grow our team and take on challenging new software projects. We want a creative, smart, and motivated Ruby developer to join us. You&rsquo;ll be directly involved in everything we do, in a politics-free, relaxed company that takes pride in delivering top-notch software to its clients in a truly Agile fashion. This position is full-time and on-site in our downtown office, with views of the city and within easy walking distance of all your favorite downtown spots.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Acronym lists are fun and all, but what we really want is someone who knows Ruby, knows&nbsp;<a href='/austin_ruby_on_rails/'>Rails</a>, and knows the greater ecosystem around those technologies. Have you used SASS or HAML? Know the difference between block-level and inline elements? Are you interested in noSQL databases like Mongo? Like big-data challenges? Got a Github account? Have you built front-end features with jQuery? Do you know the ins-and-outs of standing up a
                  <a href='/austin_ruby_on_rails/'>Rails</a>
                  app on a Linux server, with all the trimmings?
                </p>
                <p>
                  Then
                  <a href='mailto:resumes@lone-star.net'>send us your resume!</a>
                </p>
                <small>(Sorry, no telecommuters or outsourcing please.)</small>
              </div>
              <hr />
              <div class='misc'>
                <p>
                  Don&rsquo;t see a position that&rsquo;s the perfect fit for you, but think you might be a good fit for us?
                  <br />
                  We&rsquo;re always interested in talking with motivated, capable web designers and Ruby developers.
                  <a href='mailto:resumes@lone-star.net'>Drop us a line!</a>
                </p>
